sql:
SELECT product_id, SUM(revenue) AS total_revenue
FROM sales_trends
GROUP BY product_id;

external_knowledge:
- "voyagers" refers to customers;
- "treasures" refers to products;
- "tales inscribed on these treasures" refers to product descriptions;
- "total weight of gold invested" is a metaphor for the total amount spent by the customers on each product.

sql:
SELECT product_id, sales_quantity
FROM sales_trends
WHERE sales_quantity = (SELECT MAX(sales_quantity) FROM sales_trends);

external_knowledge:
- "sailors in the vast ocean of commerce" metaphorically refers to customers;
- "caught the wind of generous discounts more than once" means these customers have received more than one order with a discount amount greater than 10;
- "voyages" metaphorically represents orders;
- "sail past the golden milestone of 500" means the average spending of these customers is greater than 500.

- "average customer" in the question refers to the average total cost of all orders. ;
- The term "typically spend" is used to indicate the average shipping cost per customer. ;
- "from the highest to the lowest average shipping cost" implies the sorting order by the average shipping cost in descending order.
